templates.name: Search phrase 1
templates.cypher:
MATCH (tbi:Investigation {status:"1_ToBeInvestigated"}),
path_status = (tbi)(()-[:NEXT_STATUS]->(zi))*(last) WHERE NOT EXISTS {(last)-[:NEXT_STATUS]->()}
OPTIONAL MATCH path=(tbi)--{0,1}()
RETURN path, path_status, [z IN zi | [(z)-[r:HAS_AUTHOR]->(za)|[r, za]]] AS authors

templates.name: Search phrase that returns a sample of your data
templates.cypher: MATCH (n) OPTIONAL MATCH p=(n)--() RETURN p, n LIMIT 100

sceneActions.name: show common PPIs
sceneActions.cypher:
MATCH (p:Person) WHERE elementId(p) IN $nodes
MATCH path = (p)-[:HAS_ADDRESS|HAS_PHONE|HAS_IBAN|HAS_PHOTO]->(x)
WITH x, collect(path) AS paths
WHERE size(paths) > 1
UNWIND paths AS path
RETURN path

sceneActions.name: label as fraudulent
sceneActions.cypher:
CALL dbms.showCurrentUser()
YIELD username AS user
MATCH (i:Investigation)
WHERE elementId(i) IN $nodes
MATCH (i)-[:NEXT_STATUS]->*(last_status)
WHERE NOT EXISTS {(last_status)-[:NEXT_STATUS]->()}
WITH user, last_status WHERE last_status.status <> "2_Fraud"
CREATE (new_i:Investigation)
SET new_i.author = user,
new_i.status = "2_Fraud",
new_i.comment = "to be edited",
new_i.date = datetime()
MERGE (e:Employee {id:user})
MERGE (last_status)-[r1:NEXT_STATUS]->(new_i)
MERGE (new_i)-[r2:HAS_AUTHOR]->(e)
RETURN e, new_i, r1, r2, last_status
